1
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:41,867
<i>Didn't I tell you not
to see that woman?</i>

2
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:43,800
<i>Can't I see them even for
just a while?</i>

3
00:00:43,933 --> 00:00:44,933
<i> What did she say? What?</i>

4
00:00:45,067 --> 00:00:46,500
<i> Tell me about your plan!</i>

5
00:00:46,633 --> 00:00:47,833
<i>- Hazel!
- Because I know!</i>

6
00:00:47,967 --> 00:00:49,567
<i>- I'll find out about it anyway!
- Mom! Why are you yelling?</i>

7
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:50,733
<i> From now on,</i>

8
00:00:50,867 --> 00:00:53,400
<i>I won't let myself
get affected by you, Manuel.</i>

9
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:54,800
<i> Never.</i>

10
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:56,767
<i> Love.</i>

11
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:59,600
<i>I just want to ask for
your forgiveness personally.</i>

12
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:01,633
<i> It's too late.</i>

13
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:03,067
<i> The nerve of you!</i>

14
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,133
<i>You're a mistress!
Mistress!</i>

15
00:01:04,267 --> 00:01:05,633
<i>Felma isn't a mistress!
You know that!</i>

16
00:01:05,767 --> 00:01:07,167
<i>You're even defending
your mistress!</i>

17
00:01:08,467 --> 00:01:09,567
<i> I'm not a mistress!</i>

18
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:11,900
<i> And I will never be one!</i>

19
00:01:12,033 --> 00:01:13,767
<i>Who are you? Why are
you hurting my mother?</i>

20
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:15,400
Jeff, son.

21
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:16,933
<i> Don't touch me!</i>

22
00:01:17,067 --> 00:01:19,000
<i> Don't ever get near my mother.</i>

23
00:01:19,133 --> 00:01:20,133
<i> And your mistress, too!</i>

24
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:22,367
<i>I'm not just his mistress.
He's my husband!</i>

25
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:24,000
<i>- Get lost!
- Hey!</i>

26
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:25,233
<i> Before I hurt you!</i>

27
00:01:25,967 --> 00:01:27,100
<i> Dad is so bad.</i>

28
00:01:27,467 --> 00:01:29,233
<i>He's been hurting you until now.</i>

29
00:01:29,367 --> 00:01:30,633
<i> Jeff, that's enough.</i>

30
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,300
Let's forget what happened.

31
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,433
Can you please not tell Coleen,

32
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:44,400
and Andrea about it?

33
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:46,367
Why wouldn't we tell them, Mom?

34
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:48,800
They should know.

35
00:01:48,933 --> 00:01:50,367
They know that we came from
the hospital.

36
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:52,300
How are we going to explain
your wound?

37
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:54,033
Is it true that
you met your ex, Mom?

38
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,967
And his woman even hurt you?

39
00:01:58,233 --> 00:01:59,400
How did you know?

40
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:03,500
Susan sent me the video,
her child sent it to her.

41
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:05,533
Mom.

42
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,400
Dear.

43
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:10,900
Sweetie, I'm okay.

44
00:02:11,033 --> 00:02:11,967
I'm okay.

45
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:13,867
- Are you sure, Mom?
- I'm all good.

46
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:15,967
Where can we see those people?

47
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:17,300
I'll avenge you, Mom.

48
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:19,267
No.

49
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,500
No, no.

50
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,667
Don't worry about that.

51
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:24,667
It won't happen again.

52
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:26,600
They'll go back to Canada.

53
00:02:26,733 --> 00:02:28,200
- What?
- And then, Mom?

54
00:02:28,333 --> 00:02:30,300
Are we just going to ignore
what happened to you?

55
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:32,833
And why do you seem
to defend them?

56
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:34,433
You're the one who got hurt!

57
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:35,633
It's so obvious!

58
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Andrea...

59
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:40,500
your mother is protecting you.

60
00:02:41,167 --> 00:02:42,900
That's why she doesn't want you
to meet with your dad.

61
00:02:43,433 --> 00:02:45,967
She doesn't want you to dig up
any hard feelings.

62
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,333
I know you want
to defend your mom.

63
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:50,300
Because you love her.

64
00:02:50,433 --> 00:02:52,567
But if you attack your father...

65
00:02:54,067 --> 00:02:55,633
it'll only make things worse.

66
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,467
Maybe it's better...

67
00:02:58,333 --> 00:02:59,833
to listen
to what your mom wants.

68
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,500
Let's just forget what happened.

69
00:03:06,567 --> 00:03:08,867
Mom, aren't we going
to talk about what happened?

70
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,500
You were messy earlier.

71
00:03:10,967 --> 00:03:12,167
Tell me what happened.

72
00:03:13,033 --> 00:03:14,467
Why don't you ask your dad?

73
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:18,633
Manuel, tell your daughter.

74
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,133
Where did you go?

75
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:23,067
And why did you go there?

76
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:26,300
Come on.

77
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:27,800
We're going to be late at the
airport

78
00:03:44,533 --> 00:03:45,667
- Titang.
- Yes, Ma'am.

79
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,167
I'll close the gate.

80
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:48,167
You can now leave.

81
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,633
- Thank you.
- Yes, Ma'am.

82
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,400
Are you okay?

83
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:01,067
No, Felma.

84
00:04:04,967 --> 00:04:05,867
It wasn't only the kids,

85
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,900
who got affected by everything
that happened.

86
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:11,500
Me, too.

87
00:04:13,267 --> 00:04:15,333
I'm mad because
I couldn't protect you.

88
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:17,367
If I had known...

89
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:20,133
it was Manuel I bumped into at
the office,

90
00:04:21,633 --> 00:04:24,000
I would've made sure
you didn't leave alone.

91
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:28,633
Who would have thought that
I'd cross paths

92
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,267
with Manuel and Hazel?

93
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,567
You and Manuel,

94
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:37,133
you didn't even think
you'd bump into each other.

95
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,767
So how do you feel now?

96
00:04:48,933 --> 00:04:50,167
Actually, I'm okay.

97
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,700
When I saw Manuel...

98
00:04:56,033 --> 00:04:57,600
all my anger came flooding back.

99
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:02,267
Especially when Hazel showed up.

100
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:05,033
But after what happened...

101
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:09,633
I felt better.

102
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:12,100
Jeff, I want to get justice
for Mom.

103
00:05:12,233 --> 00:05:13,233
I want that even more.

104
00:05:14,167 --> 00:05:16,267
I saw how that demon hurt Mom.

105
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,800
But Mom said we should respect
her decision.

106
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,267
Let's just forget what happened.

107
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:26,033
I was able to tell Manuel
everything I wanted to say.

108
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:30,867
I ended up releasing
all my anger on Hazel.

109
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:35,033
I finally let go of all
the pent-up anger in my heart.

110
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,400
I seemed to have closure.

111
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:43,333
So, are you ready to forgive
Manuel now?

112
00:05:45,167 --> 00:05:47,867
Coleen, can you stop being so
stubborn?

113
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,500
I won't call your godfather.

114
00:05:50,633 --> 00:05:52,400
Auntie, please, ask Uncle,

115
00:05:52,533 --> 00:05:54,533
where I could find Dad.

116
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:57,267
- Coleen.
- Please, Auntie.

117
00:05:57,533 --> 00:05:58,933
Coleen, that's enough!
That's your second strike.

118
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,467
First, the pictures
you gave to Miss Abby.

119
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,733
We're not done with it yet!

120
00:06:03,333 --> 00:06:05,433
And now you're doing
something else?

121
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:07,100
Mom got hurt,

122
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:08,933
and yet you still want to meet
with your dad!

123
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:10,667
Mom's doing okay!

124
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,333
And it wasn't Dad who hurt her.

125
00:06:13,467 --> 00:06:14,367
It was Hazel!

126
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:16,633
I only want to see Dad.

127
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:19,233
And then, what?

128
00:06:19,867 --> 00:06:21,233
You'll expect to have
communication with him?

129
00:06:21,367 --> 00:06:22,433
You two will talk?

130
00:06:23,233 --> 00:06:25,100
Your dad's wife is Satan's
sister.

131
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:26,533
Your dream will never come true!

132
00:06:26,667 --> 00:06:27,767
Jeff!

133
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:29,867
I know you guys hate him.

134
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,733
But should I hate him, too?

135
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:34,433
And please!

136
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:36,300
I'm no longer a kid!

137
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:38,667
I can decide for myself!

138
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,400
These feelings are mine!
This life is mine!

139
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:42,033
- What did you say?
- Jeff!

140
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:45,500
Hold on! What happened here?

141
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:46,700
Wait!

142
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:48,033
Are you going
to hurt your sister?

143
00:06:49,433 --> 00:06:52,933
Jeff, I didn't raise you
to hurt other people.

144
00:06:53,233 --> 00:06:55,667
Especially women, especially
your sister!

145
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,233
And you, Coleen!

146
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:06,467
When did you learn to talk back
to your siblings?

147
00:07:09,267 --> 00:07:10,633
I know.

148
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,867
I know you long for your father.

149
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:17,167
But he already has
another family.

150
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:20,800
Don't insist on seeing him.

151
00:07:24,033 --> 00:07:25,000
Dear.

152
00:07:34,667 --> 00:07:35,833
I don't want this
to happen again.

153
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:40,533
Apologize to each other.

154
00:07:45,267 --> 00:07:47,300
- Sorry.
- Jeff, sorry.

155
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:49,433
I just don't want you
to get hurt.

156
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,567
I'm just protecting you.

157
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:54,867
Please stop crying.

158
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,267
Andrea, sorry.

159
00:08:02,033 --> 00:08:03,067
It's okay.

160
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,333
Everything's good now.

161
00:08:24,433 --> 00:08:26,167
Mom, Dad.

162
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:28,600
You didn't talk
the entire flight.

163
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,400
You didn't talk
the entire flight.

164
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:32,733
What's really the problem?

165
00:08:33,467 --> 00:08:34,167
Fine.

166
00:08:36,033 --> 00:08:38,067
Your dad met with his woman.

167
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:39,867
Woman?

168
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:41,900
As in mistress?

169
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:46,833
Dad, do you have a mistress?

170
00:08:46,967 --> 00:08:48,333
Sweetie, she's not my mistress.

171
00:08:48,467 --> 00:08:49,533
- You know, the truth is...
- What?

172
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:50,733
What do you mean by not your
mistress?

173
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,767
During your grandma's funeral,

174
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,500
your dad did nothing
but contact his mistress,

175
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:57,767
so they could meet.

176
00:08:57,900 --> 00:08:59,667
And when I caught them,
what did I get?

177
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:00,667
This!

178
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:03,000
I got hurt while your dad
was just watching.

179
00:09:03,133 --> 00:09:04,333
Hazel, that's not true!

180
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:07,633
Jessica!

181
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:12,833
You just want to make me look
bad in front of our child!

182
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:15,367
Felma isn't my mistress!

183
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:16,500
We were together
before you came!

184
00:09:18,033 --> 00:09:19,433
But you two are not married.

185
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:21,100
We are.

186
00:09:21,667 --> 00:09:23,133
So no matter what you say,
she's a mistress.

187
00:09:23,667 --> 00:09:25,033
Lover. Kept woman.

188
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:29,267
This conversation
won't go anywhere.

189
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,400
Good morning, Madam.

190
00:09:46,733 --> 00:09:47,933
Madam, my foot.

191
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:50,100
Come here.

192
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:53,000
What do you need?

193
00:09:57,833 --> 00:09:59,567
So, how are you, Felma?

194
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:02,067
How was your confrontation
with Manuel

195
00:10:02,233 --> 00:10:04,467
and his witch wife?

196
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,467
Did you get closure?

197
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,633
Of course, Paz.

198
00:10:09,067 --> 00:10:10,367
Very good.

199
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:14,000
So, whenever I mention Manuel to
you,

200
00:10:14,133 --> 00:10:15,233
you will never
get agitated again?

201
00:10:16,767 --> 00:10:18,067
Never. I can handle it.

202
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,300
Excellent!

203
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:22,233
So, does it mean I can now push
Noah to court you?

204
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,100
What are you saying?

205
00:10:30,733 --> 00:10:31,933
Madam, can you please check
this?

206
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:33,100
Madam, my foot.

207
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:35,000
Stop calling me "Madam"!

208
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:38,100
Come on, Paz!

209
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:44,333
Go away, Dad!

210
00:10:45,067 --> 00:10:46,667
I don't wanna talk to you!

211
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,133
Go away!

212
00:10:48,933 --> 00:10:50,833
Dad, go away!

213
00:10:51,867 --> 00:10:53,000
I said go!

214
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:56,500
Mom.

215
00:10:57,667 --> 00:11:00,500
Mom, I can't believe dad
has a mistress.

216
00:11:00,733 --> 00:11:02,867
How did that happen?

217
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:06,167
Mom.

218
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:11,000
How did that happen, Mom?

219
00:11:12,433 --> 00:11:17,933
He told me he was single when he
started courting.

220
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:20,800
And then,

221
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,100
I fell madly in love with him.

222
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:27,833
I got pregnant.

223
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,433
But one day,

224
00:11:32,533 --> 00:11:34,933
I received a call
from the Philippines.

225
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:37,133
Someone was looking for him.

226
00:11:38,933 --> 00:11:41,200
She said she was
your dad's wife.

227
00:11:43,467 --> 00:11:44,800
She fought me.

228
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:48,733
She made it seem like
I'm the mistress.

229
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:54,400
She told me that I stole her
husband.

230
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:57,967
But Jessica, that's not true.

231
00:11:58,933 --> 00:12:00,967
Because they're not married.

232
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,167
You know what...

233
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:09,833
your dad lied to us.

234
00:12:11,033 --> 00:12:14,167
He made me believe that I was
the only one.

235
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:17,400
He made me believe
that I was the only one.

236
00:12:17,533 --> 00:12:19,633
That we're the only ones
in his life.

237
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:22,800
I thought when he married me...

238
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:26,800
he ended his relationship with
that woman.

239
00:12:28,567 --> 00:12:32,633
But, Jessica, he made that woman
his mistress.

240
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,800
And the most painful
part of it is...

241
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:40,467
that they still have a secret
communication.

242
00:12:41,633 --> 00:12:44,433
Mom, I hate Dad.

243
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,700
Mom, I hate Dad. I hate him!

244
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:51,533
I hate Dad!

245
00:12:53,567 --> 00:12:55,467
I hate him so much.

246
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:58,200
I hate him! I hate him!

247
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:00,333
That's enough.

248
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:07,733
Jeffrey?

249
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:08,867
Son!

250
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:11,867
You need to talk to me?

251
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,033
I want to ask for your advice,
Mom.

252
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:20,767
I want to go and see
Daisy and Tetay again.

253
00:13:23,267 --> 00:13:25,567
Even though Andrea teased me
the other day,

254
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:26,700
she was right.

255
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,967
I'm like dad,
who left his family.

256
00:13:33,867 --> 00:13:36,833
And when Coleen and I fought,

257
00:13:36,967 --> 00:13:38,100
I saw my daughter in her.

258
00:13:41,167 --> 00:13:42,600
They both grew up
without a father.

259
00:13:45,167 --> 00:13:47,367
That's why I don't want Tetay
to grow old without a father.

260
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,300
I will never be like dad.

261
00:13:53,533 --> 00:13:54,767
You know what, Jeffrey?

262
00:13:54,933 --> 00:13:56,867
That's one of the things I've
been praying for.

263
00:13:59,667 --> 00:14:01,267
That you'll fix your family.

264
00:14:03,067 --> 00:14:05,267
If you're asking for my advice,

265
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:10,167
I just want to tell you,
do not prolong it.

266
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:15,367
Go and see your family.

267
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,667
And don't ever back down.

268
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:36,333
Daisy.

269
00:14:39,033 --> 00:14:40,100
What are you doing here?

270
00:14:40,967 --> 00:14:41,933
How did you know...

271
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,700
- Leave!
- No, no, Daisy.

272
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:45,467
I just want us to talk.

273
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:49,533
And I also want to see Tetay.

274
00:14:50,467 --> 00:14:51,633
You can't!

275
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:55,033
Get out of here!
Get lost!

276
00:14:56,367 --> 00:14:58,767
Leave before Lance sees you.

277
00:15:00,433 --> 00:15:01,300
Lance?

278
00:15:03,867 --> 00:15:05,533
Who is Lance?
Your boyfriend?

279
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:07,367
Daisy!

280
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:08,833
What's taking you so long?

281
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:10,367
Are you talking with someone?

282
00:15:11,533 --> 00:15:12,467
Daisy!

283
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,333
- Let go of me!
- Daisy! Daisy!

284
00:15:14,467 --> 00:15:16,067
- Wait!
- Daisy!

285
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:20,533
- Daisy!
- Why do you have a bruise?

286
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,767
Daisy, why do you have a bruise?

287
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:24,833
Is he hurting you?

288
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:27,033
Daisy!

289
00:15:27,467 --> 00:15:29,300
Daisy, let's talk first-
Why do you have a bruise?

290
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:35,767
Hazel!

291
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,033
Jessica's missing!

292
00:15:38,933 --> 00:15:40,500
- What?
- Hazel!

293
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:42,533
Jessica's missing.

294
00:15:42,667 --> 00:15:44,500
She left her phone in her room.

295
00:15:44,733 --> 00:15:45,367
What?

296
00:15:45,633 --> 00:15:46,467
Maybe she's just with her
friends.

297
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:47,667
Call them.

298
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:49,533
- You're overreacting.
- Yes, I called...

299
00:15:49,667 --> 00:15:51,100
Ivy and Belle.

300
00:15:51,233 --> 00:15:52,300
But they don't know
where she is.

301
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:55,667
Wait, I'll call Eva.

302
00:15:56,367 --> 00:15:57,000
There.

303
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:01,300
Yes.

304
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:03,633
Eva, good evening.

305
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:07,267
Sorry to call you this late,
but...

306
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:11,700
You know, Jessica
left our house and...

307
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:15,833
Oh, yes, I would like
to ask if she's with you?

308
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,100
Oh, okay.

309
00:16:21,867 --> 00:16:23,000
Thank you, thank you very much.

310
00:16:25,867 --> 00:16:27,267
Ava.

311
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:28,700
Not Eva.

312
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:29,700
Come on!

313
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:31,033
She probably didn't understand

314
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:32,467
because of your broken English.

315
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:33,900
You know, instead of insulting
me

316
00:16:34,033 --> 00:16:37,033
you could'vecall Jessica's other
friends

317
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:38,900
Oh, yes.

318
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:41,867
You don't know who our
daughter's friends are.

319
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,667
This is all your fault!

320
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:46,467
If you didn't meet with Felma,

321
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,833
Jessica wouldn't leave the
house.

322
00:16:48,067 --> 00:16:49,267
Why are you blaming me?

323
00:16:50,167 --> 00:16:51,300
It was both our fault.

324
00:16:51,433 --> 00:16:53,133
You shouldn't have gotten
Jessica involved.

325
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,533
Oh, Mrs. Wilson is calling.

326
00:16:58,967 --> 00:17:00,000
Yes.

327
00:17:00,467 --> 00:17:02,133
Good evening, Mrs. Wilson.

328
00:17:04,867 --> 00:17:06,000
Thank you, thank you very much.

329
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:09,333
Who is Mrs. Wilson?

330
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:11,967
Don't tell me, even here in
Canada

331
00:17:12,100 --> 00:17:13,267
you also have a mistress?

332
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,400
For heaven's sake, Hazel!

333
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,033
She is the grandmother of
Jessica's friend!

334
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:21,200
She's the one giving me
a part-time job.

335
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:23,900
Part-time?

336
00:17:25,067 --> 00:17:26,500
Wait, you're working?

337
00:17:28,367 --> 00:17:30,167
Yes, whenever
Jessica's at school.

338
00:17:30,767 --> 00:17:32,867
I work part-time
at Mr. and Mrs. Wilson's house.

339
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:36,833
I do gardening and fix their
broken stuff.

340
00:17:36,967 --> 00:17:38,567
I also care for their dogs.

341
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:41,033
Wait, we never talked about you
getting a job.

342
00:17:41,167 --> 00:17:42,200
Since when did you start
working?

343
00:17:42,333 --> 00:17:43,667
Why aren't you telling me?

344
00:17:44,033 --> 00:17:45,533
Hazel, can you please stop!

345
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:46,933
Our daughter is missing,

346
00:17:47,067 --> 00:17:48,433
and yet you're concerned
with other things!

347
00:17:55,033 --> 00:17:56,367
Yes, Mom.
I'm still here.

348
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,233
Have you already
talked to Daisy?

349
00:17:59,067 --> 00:18:00,300
I haven't, Mom.

350
00:18:00,767 --> 00:18:02,400
We still haven't talked yet.

351
00:18:02,667 --> 00:18:04,100
You've been there for hours,
Jeffrey.

352
00:18:04,733 --> 00:18:05,567
Yes, quite a bit.

353
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:07,067
I need to wait for her.

354
00:18:09,067 --> 00:18:09,967
Mom...

355
00:18:11,033 --> 00:18:12,067
I'll just call you again,

356
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:14,400
Okay, do your best!

357
00:18:15,133 --> 00:18:15,900
Okay. Bye.

358
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:28,333
Your helmet.

359
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:32,167
No kiss?

360
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:35,100
Come on!

361
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:39,300
I knew you'd give it.

362
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:40,800
You're just making things
harder.

363
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:42,800
I'll call you later.

364
00:18:42,933 --> 00:18:43,667
Make sure to cook a meal.

365
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:10,900
Yes, Mom.
I'm almost home.

366
00:19:11,333 --> 00:19:13,433
Okay, bye, Mom.
I love you.

367
00:19:16,233 --> 00:19:17,867
- Tetay?
- Dad!

368
00:19:24,767 --> 00:19:26,000
Tetay, sorry for all the wrong
things I did

369
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:27,333
to you and your mom.

370
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:28,833
Sorry.

371
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:30,633
Sorry.

372
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:32,267
Tetay?

373
00:19:33,667 --> 00:19:34,667
Tetay!

374
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:38,100
Tetay, get inside the house.

375
00:19:38,533 --> 00:19:40,767
Dad's here, Mom.

376
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:42,567
I said get inside.

377
00:19:44,467 --> 00:19:45,600
Bye, Dad.

378
00:19:45,733 --> 00:19:46,867
I'll take care of this, Tetay.

379
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,000
Daisy, wait.

380
00:19:50,167 --> 00:19:51,767
I know Lance is hurting you.

381
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,300
I saw your bruise.
Why are you letting him?

382
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:55,967
I'm not letting him.

383
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:57,700
I fight with him.

384
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:00,767
Daisy, how can you
even fight him?

385
00:20:02,233 --> 00:20:02,967
How?

386
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,100
Does he hurt Tetay, too?

387
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:06,567
No.

388
00:20:07,433 --> 00:20:08,767
He better not even try.

389
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:11,233
We'll kill each other before
that.

390
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:18,867
Daisy, I know I don't have the
right to interfere

391
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,167
with your decisions.

392
00:20:21,267 --> 00:20:23,333
But at least find
someone decent.

393
00:20:23,933 --> 00:20:24,733
One who's responsible.

394
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:27,467
What about you, Jeffrey?

395
00:20:29,533 --> 00:20:30,600
Are you even decent?

396
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:34,600
Sorry, Daisy.

397
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:37,167
I hope you can forgive me.

398
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:38,133
That's the reason I'm here.

399
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:39,333
because...

400
00:20:39,567 --> 00:20:41,300
I want to correct all the wrong
things I did to you and Tetay.

401
00:20:43,100 --> 00:20:44,100
Really?

402
00:20:44,767 --> 00:20:45,600
I'm listening.

403
00:20:46,067 --> 00:20:47,133
Like how?

404
00:20:47,567 --> 00:20:48,733
I'll take you back...

405
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:50,467
from Lance.

406
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:55,900
Are you joking?

407
00:20:57,867 --> 00:20:59,800
Do you think I'm still the dumb
woman who was in love with you,

408
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:00,900
nine years ago?

409
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:03,267
A lot has changed.

410
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:04,867
I'm a different woman now.

411
00:21:06,433 --> 00:21:07,600
And you too.

412
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:10,233
We no longer know each other.

413
00:21:13,033 --> 00:21:15,033
That's why I'll introduce myself
again to you.

414
00:21:21,667 --> 00:21:22,833
I'll court you again.

415
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:27,867
You and Tetay.

416
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:32,000
For real, Dad?

417
00:21:32,133 --> 00:21:33,733
Are you going to pursue
mom and me?

418
00:21:34,067 --> 00:21:35,400
My answer is yes!

419
00:21:35,533 --> 00:21:36,567
She already said yes.

420
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:39,333
Tetay, don't be stubborn.

421
00:21:39,467 --> 00:21:40,367
Get inside.

422
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:41,833
Wait, Mom.

423
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,600
Accept my dad first.

424
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:46,267
So we can be one happy family
again.

425
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:49,133
Break up with Boss Lance.

426
00:21:53,933 --> 00:21:54,767
Tetay, dear, why....

427
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:58,067
Why do you call him Boss Lance?

428
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,833
That's what he wants.

429
00:22:01,267 --> 00:22:04,400
And he's also mom's boss
in the call center.

430
00:22:04,533 --> 00:22:05,400
Tetay!

431
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:06,733
You're so talkative.

432
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:07,433
Let's go!

433
00:22:07,567 --> 00:22:08,733
I'm just telling the truth.

434
00:22:08,867 --> 00:22:10,167
Tetay, dear, I'll get you back.

435
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:11,800
Daisy, I'm serious.
I'm going to win you over.

436
00:22:12,133 --> 00:22:13,667
You and Tetay. Daisy!

437
00:22:13,967 --> 00:22:14,933
- Give it your all, Dad!
- Daisy, let's talk...

438
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:17,833
We still have a lot of things to
talk about, Daisy!

439
00:22:18,067 --> 00:22:18,867
Tetay!

440
00:22:19,533 --> 00:22:20,400
Daisy!

441
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:22,500
I'll wait.

442
00:22:32,567 --> 00:22:34,133
Thank you, Mr.
and Mrs. Wilson...

443
00:22:34,267 --> 00:22:36,667
for letting my daughter
stay here.

444
00:22:37,033 --> 00:22:37,867
Don't bother.

445
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,867
We understand,
<i> these things happen.</i>

446
00:22:41,367 --> 00:22:42,133
<i> Sorry, Dear.</i>

447
00:22:42,267 --> 00:22:43,967
We didn't want your dad
to worry.

448
00:22:44,767 --> 00:22:46,867
We'll leave you two alone here
to talk.

449
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:49,033
Let's go.

450
00:22:50,933 --> 00:22:51,800
Dad.

451
00:22:59,667 --> 00:23:01,433
- How are you, Jessica?
- You know what, Dad?

452
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:02,967
All of my friends think,

453
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:05,367
that I have the best dad
in the world.

454
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:07,200
But turns out it's a lie.

455
00:23:08,833 --> 00:23:10,067
You know what, Jessica?

456
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:13,967
When your mom and I
met in Saudi Arabia,

457
00:23:15,067 --> 00:23:18,100
she knew that I had a family.

458
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:20,833
Family?

459
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:22,033
What do you mean?

460
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:40,167
You have children?

461
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:46,033
2007.

462
00:23:46,933 --> 00:23:49,700
Dad, this picture
is already old.

463
00:23:51,133 --> 00:23:52,333
Which means...

464
00:23:53,567 --> 00:23:57,667
these kids here
are older than me?

465
00:24:00,367 --> 00:24:00,967
Yes.

466
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,300
You have an older brother and
older sisters

467
00:24:04,433 --> 00:24:05,600
in the Philippines.

468
00:24:05,733 --> 00:24:06,833
Then why did you marry mom,

469
00:24:06,967 --> 00:24:08,800
if you already had a family?

470
00:24:08,933 --> 00:24:10,367
Jessica, it's because...

471
00:24:10,833 --> 00:24:12,400
I got your mom pregnant.

472
00:24:13,067 --> 00:24:16,767
And Saudi Arabia
has strict laws.

473
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:20,567
So I wasn't born out of love?

474
00:24:22,933 --> 00:24:26,167
You got mom pregnant
and only married her,

475
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:27,967
because of some law?

476
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:30,567
Dad, you didn't want me?

477
00:24:30,733 --> 00:24:32,233
- No.
- Dad.

478
00:24:32,667 --> 00:24:33,667
No, Jessica.

479
00:24:34,233 --> 00:24:37,067
The situation between your mom,
Felma,

480
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:39,233
and me was a total mess.

481
00:24:40,167 --> 00:24:42,400
It was so messy.

482
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:44,833
But you were not
part of that mess.

483
00:24:46,033 --> 00:24:48,600
Because even before you were
born, I already wanted you.

484
00:24:48,733 --> 00:24:49,967
I already loved you.

485
00:24:51,633 --> 00:24:52,467
How about mom?

486
00:24:53,967 --> 00:24:55,767
Don't you love her?

487
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:00,533
Jessica...

488
00:25:02,833 --> 00:25:05,067
I tried to love your mom.

489
00:25:06,433 --> 00:25:08,133
I tried to teach my heart.

490
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:14,233
We've been together for a long
time, but...

491
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:17,733
I can't get Felma off my mind.

492
00:25:18,933 --> 00:25:20,333
And your siblings...

493
00:25:21,767 --> 00:25:24,167
I've hurt them so badly.

494
00:25:24,833 --> 00:25:26,233
That's why...

495
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:28,467
when we came home to Manila,

496
00:25:30,967 --> 00:25:32,867
I tried to meet with them,

497
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,733
so I could ask for forgiveness.

498
00:25:36,100 --> 00:25:38,633
Not to get back together
with Felma.

499
00:25:39,167 --> 00:25:42,733
Dad, do you still love
your first wife?

500
00:25:46,667 --> 00:25:48,333
Dear, I can no longer love her.

501
00:25:50,867 --> 00:25:52,433
I'm married to your mom.

502
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,233
Why would you make up stories
just to turn me against Dad?

503
00:26:05,367 --> 00:26:07,133
Suddenly your dad's the hero?

504
00:26:07,267 --> 00:26:09,267
I'm the one feeding you!

505
00:26:09,433 --> 00:26:11,233
Mommy, you're so mean!

506
00:26:11,367 --> 00:26:12,567
What now, huh?

507
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:15,933
Sorry if I couldn't repay all
your kindness.

508
00:26:16,067 --> 00:26:17,567
Do you love me too, Felma?

509
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:19,567
I feel like a loser, Alice.

510
00:26:19,700 --> 00:26:21,633
Because, despite my efforts...

511
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:23,633
Manuel still can't learn
to love me.

512
00:26:23,767 --> 00:26:25,500
Why don't you divorce Manuel?

513
00:26:25,633 --> 00:26:26,700
I've fallen in love with Manuel.

514
00:26:26,833 --> 00:26:28,033
Did you go through my things?

515
00:26:28,167 --> 00:26:29,133
Are you looking for this?

516
00:26:29,267 --> 00:26:30,700
Why did you burn it?

517
00:26:30,833 --> 00:26:32,433
You're so evil, Hazel!

518
00:26:32,567 --> 00:26:34,200
That's why it's so difficult
to love you!

519
00:26:34,333 --> 00:26:35,133
What did you say?

520
00:26:35,267 --> 00:26:37,333
It's so difficult to love you!
